<h1>PCs</h1>
<p><a href="../icons/desktop-computer.png"><img src="../icons/desktop-computer.png" width="200"/></a></p>
<p>PCs are your typical end host devices.</p>
<h2>Menus</h2>
<p>Each PC has 4 menus to interact with it:</p>
<h3>Configure PC</h3>
<p>In this menu, you can configure: <br>
&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; - Hostname <br>
&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; - MAC Address <br>
&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; - IP Information such as: <br>
&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; - IPv4 Address and Subnet Mask <br>
&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;  - IPv6 Address and Prefix Length <br>
&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;  - Default Gateways <br></p>
<h3>Terminal</h3>
<p>The terminal allows you to interact with the PC. Currently, the available commands are: <br>
&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; - arp -a<br>
&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; - ping A.B.C.D<br>
&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; - ping A.B.C.D -n #pingcount<br></p>
<h3>Disconnect Cable</h3>
<p>This button disconnects the ethernet connection to another device.  </p>
<h3>Delete Node</h3>
<p>This button disconnects all connections, and deletes the node, and its configurations.
<strong>This cannot be undone</strong>. </p>